events.name: Google I/O extended Cebu
events.description:
Google I/O is an annual software developer-focused conference which features a keynote on the latest updates and announcements by Google. The conference also hosts in-depth sessions focused on building web, mobile, and enterprise applications with Google and open web technologies such as Android, Chrome, Chrome OS, Google APIs, Google Web Toolkit, and App Engine.

Google I/O 2017 was held last May 17-19 at the Shoreline Amphitheatre in Mountain View, California. At its 11th year, Google I/O 2017 gathered more than 7,000 attendees from all over the world. Highlights of the event include the release of Actions on Google, new standalone virtual reality headset, Android Go, Android O, and updates of Firebase, TensorFlow, Google Home and Google Photos.

REGISTER NOW AT http://ioextended.gdgcebu.org

venue.address_1: (formerly Cebu Insitute of Technology) N. Bacalso Avenue, Cebu City,  Tel +63 32 261-7741, www.cit.edu

events.description:
• What we'll do
The Mobile Sites certification is a professional accreditation that Google offers to individuals who demonstrate proficiency in basic and advanced aspects of mobile website design and development. A Mobile Sites certification allows individuals to demonstrate that Google recognizes them as an expert in mobile sites. To become certified in Mobile Sites, you need to pass the Mobile Sites exam.

This Study Jam includes talks and study sessions to better prepare the participants for the Mobile Sites certification.

• What to bring
Laptop, if available. Access to a laptop or computer is required to take the Mobile Sites certification.

• Important to know

events.name: Google I/O Extended Cebu 2018
events.description:
Welcome to Google I/O Extended Visayas Roadshow!

We are very excited to announce that this is the 7th consecutive Google I/O Extended in Cebu!

Google I/O is an annual event hosted by Google to highlight the latest in technology and product innovation. This covers topics such as the IoT, working with material design, advancements in mobile technology, and more.

Google encourages other communities to create our own recap-event featuring talks and hands-on workshop on the latest technologies. In Cebu, we take this opportunity to stream the keynote from Google, but also to pull together Cebu's growing tech community. This year's Google I/O Extended will be hosted at Oakridge Business Park in one of their main venue, The Oakridge Pavillion.

The conference will be different from I/O's of the past, with a focus on networking, good food, and an atmosphere for learning. This year, GDG Cebu made I/O extended a paid event to level up the experience for everyone and making sure they get the best of the conference experience.

Your registration will get you access to all activities on that day of the event - including lunch, refreshments, and after-party for those attending the evening. We'll also be hosting a booth doing complementary, professional head-shot photos, so dress for success and get ready to level up your tech conference experience!

To complete your registration, make sure to get an Eventbrite ticket. Click here for the complete event details: https://ioxcebu18.gdgcebu.org/

events.name: Google I/O Extended Dumaguete 2018
events.description:

We are very excited to announce that this is the 2nd consecutive Google I/O Extended in Dumaguete!

Secure your seat now at: http://iox2018dumaguete.eventbrite.com

Google I/O is an annual event hosted by Google to highlight the latest in technology and product innovation. This covers topics such as the IoT, working with material design, advancements in mobile technology, and more.

Google encourages other communities to create our own recap-event featuring talks and hands-on workshop on the latest technologies. In Dumaguete, we'll take this opportunity to stream the keynote from Google, but also to pull together Dumaguete's local tech community.

The conference will be different from I/O's of the past, with a focus on networking, good food, and an atmosphere for learning. This year, GDG Cebu made I/O extended a paid event to level up the experience for everyone and making sure they get the best of the conference experience.

Your registration will get you access to all activities on that day of the event - including lunch, refreshments, and after-party for those attending the evening. We'll also be hosting a booth doing complementary, professional head-shot photos, so dress for success and get ready to level up your tech conference experience!

Registration Fees

This year, GDG Cebu decided to take our events to the next level. We believe learning should be always free. However, to provide you the best environment, food, and swags, we need to collect fees that will ensure you have the best experience. We have a variety of online tickets specific to your current status.

Register now at http://iox2018dumaguete.eventbrite.com
